    344 uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;

    347 IN vec3 aPosition;

    361 `,Um=`#define PI 3.141592
    362 
    363 precision highp float;
    364 precision highp int;
    365 
    366 uniform mat4 uViewMatrix;
    367 
    368 uniform bool uUseLighting;
    369 
    370 uniform int uAmbientLightCount;
    371 uniform vec3 uAmbientColor[5];
    372 uniform mat3 uCameraRotation;
    373 uniform int uDirectionalLightCount;
    374 uniform vec3 uLightingDirection[5];
    375 uniform vec3 uDirectionalDiffuseColors[5];
    376 uniform vec3 uDirectionalSpecularColors[5];
    377 
    378 uniform int uPointLightCount;
    379 uniform vec3 uPointLightLocation[5];
    380 uniform vec3 uPointLightDiffuseColors[5];	
    381 uniform vec3 uPointLightSpecularColors[5];
    382 
    383 uniform int uSpotLightCount;
    384 uniform float uSpotLightAngle[5];
    385 uniform float uSpotLightConc[5];
    386 uniform vec3 uSpotLightDiffuseColors[5];
    387 uniform vec3 uSpotLightSpecularColors[5];
    388 uniform vec3 uSpotLightLocation[5];
    389 uniform vec3 uSpotLightDirection[5];
    390 
    391 uniform bool uSpecular;
    392 uniform float uShininess;
    393 uniform float uMetallic;
    394 
    395 uniform float uConstantAttenuation;
    396 uniform float uLinearAttenuation;
    397 uniform float uQuadraticAttenuation;
    398 
    399 // setting from  _setImageLightUniforms()
    400 // boolean to initiate the calculateImageDiffuse and calculateImageSpecular
    401 uniform bool uUseImageLight;
    402 // texture for use in calculateImageDiffuse
    403 uniform sampler2D environmentMapDiffused;
    404 // texture for use in calculateImageSpecular
    405 uniform sampler2D environmentMapSpecular;
    406 
    407 const float specularFactor = 2.0;
    408 const float diffuseFactor = 0.73;
    409 
    410 struct LightResult {
    411   float specular;
    412   float diffuse;
    413 };
    414 
    415 float _phongSpecular(
    416   vec3 lightDirection,
    417   vec3 viewDirection,
    418   vec3 surfaceNormal,
    419   float shininess) {
    420 
    421   vec3 R = reflect(lightDirection, surfaceNormal);
    422   return pow(max(0.0, dot(R, viewDirection)), shininess);
    423 }
    424 
    425 float _lambertDiffuse(vec3 lightDirection, vec3 surfaceNormal) {
    426   return max(0.0, dot(-lightDirection, surfaceNormal));
    427 }
    428 
    429 LightResult _light(vec3 viewDirection, vec3 normal, vec3 lightVector, float shininess, float metallic) {
    430 
    431   vec3 lightDir = normalize(lightVector);
    432 
    433   //compute our diffuse & specular terms
    434   LightResult lr;
    435   float specularIntensity = mix(1.0, 0.4, metallic);
    436   float diffuseIntensity = mix(1.0, 0.1, metallic);
    437   if (uSpecular)
    438     lr.specular = (_phongSpecular(lightDir, viewDirection, normal, shininess)) * specularIntensity;
    439     lr.diffuse = _lambertDiffuse(lightDir, normal) * diffuseIntensity;
    440   return lr;
    441 }
    442 
    443 // converts the range of "value" from [min1 to max1] to [min2 to max2]
    444 float map(float value, float min1, float max1, float min2, float max2) {
    445   return min2 + (value - min1) * (max2 - min2) / (max1 - min1);
    446 }
    447 
    448 vec2 mapTextureToNormal( vec3 v ){
    449   // x = r sin(phi) cos(theta)   
    450   // y = r cos(phi)  
    451   // z = r sin(phi) sin(theta)
    452   float phi = acos( v.y );
    453   // if phi is 0, then there are no x, z components
    454   float theta = 0.0;
    455   // else 
    456   theta = acos(v.x / sin(phi));
    457   float sinTheta = v.z / sin(phi);
    458   if (sinTheta < 0.0) {
    459     // Turn it into -theta, but in the 0-2PI range
    460     theta = 2.0 * PI - theta;
    461   }
    462   theta = theta / (2.0 * 3.14159);
    463   phi = phi / 3.14159 ;
    464   
    465   vec2 angles = vec2( fract(theta + 0.25), 1.0 - phi );
    466   return angles;
    467 }
    468 
    469 
    470 vec3 calculateImageDiffuse(vec3 vNormal, vec3 vViewPosition, float metallic){
    471   // make 2 seperate builds 
    472   vec3 worldCameraPosition =  vec3(0.0, 0.0, 0.0);  // hardcoded world camera position
    473   vec3 worldNormal = normalize(vNormal * uCameraRotation);
    474   vec2 newTexCoor = mapTextureToNormal( worldNormal );
    475   vec4 texture = TEXTURE( environmentMapDiffused, newTexCoor );
    476   // this is to make the darker sections more dark
    477   // png and jpg usually flatten the brightness so it is to reverse that
    478   return mix(smoothstep(vec3(0.0), vec3(1.0), texture.xyz), vec3(0.0), metallic);
    479 }
    480 
    481 vec3 calculateImageSpecular(vec3 vNormal, vec3 vViewPosition, float shininess, float metallic){
    482   vec3 worldCameraPosition =  vec3(0.0, 0.0, 0.0);
    483   vec3 worldNormal = normalize(vNormal);
    484   vec3 lightDirection = normalize( vViewPosition - worldCameraPosition );
    485   vec3 R = reflect(lightDirection, worldNormal) * uCameraRotation;
    486   vec2 newTexCoor = mapTextureToNormal( R );
    487 #ifdef WEBGL2
    488   // In p5js the range of shininess is >= 1,
    489   // Therefore roughness range will be ([0,1]*8)*20 or [0, 160]
    490   // The factor of 8 is because currently the getSpecularTexture
    491   // only calculated 8 different levels of roughness
    492   // The factor of 20 is just to spread up this range so that,
    493   // [1, max] of shininess is converted to [0,160] of roughness
    494   float roughness = 20. / shininess;
    495   vec4 outColor = textureLod(environmentMapSpecular, newTexCoor, roughness * 8.);
    496 #else
    497   vec4 outColor = TEXTURE(environmentMapSpecular, newTexCoor);
    498 #endif
    499   // this is to make the darker sections more dark
    500   // png and jpg usually flatten the brightness so it is to reverse that
    501   return mix(
    502     pow(outColor.xyz, vec3(10)),
    503     pow(outColor.xyz, vec3(1.2)),
    504     metallic 
    505   );
    506 }
    507 
    508 void totalLight(
    509   vec3 modelPosition,
    510   vec3 normal,
    511   float shininess,
    512   float metallic,
    513   out vec3 totalDiffuse,
    514   out vec3 totalSpecular
    515 ) {
    516 
    517   totalSpecular = vec3(0.0);
    518 
    519   if (!uUseLighting) {
    520     totalDiffuse = vec3(1.0);
    521     return;
    522   }
    523 
    524   totalDiffuse = vec3(0.0);
    525 
    526   vec3 viewDirection = normalize(-modelPosition);
    527 
    528   for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
    529     if (j < uDirectionalLightCount) {
    530       vec3 lightVector = (uViewMatrix * vec4(uLightingDirection[j], 0.0)).xyz;
    531       vec3 lightColor = uDirectionalDiffuseColors[j];
    532       vec3 specularColor = uDirectionalSpecularColors[j];
    533       LightResult result = _light(viewDirection, normal, lightVector, shininess, metallic);
    534       totalDiffuse += result.diffuse * lightColor;
    535       totalSpecular += result.specular * lightColor * specularColor;
    536     }
    537 
    538     if (j < uPointLightCount) {
    539       vec3 lightPosition = (uViewMatrix * vec4(uPointLightLocation[j], 1.0)).xyz;
    540       vec3 lightVector = modelPosition - lightPosition;
    541       //calculate attenuation
    542       float lightDistance = length(lightVector);
    543       float lightFalloff = 1.0 / (uConstantAttenuation + lightDistance * uLinearAttenuation + (lightDistance * lightDistance) * uQuadraticAttenuation);
    544       vec3 lightColor = lightFalloff * uPointLightDiffuseColors[j];
    545       vec3 specularColor = lightFalloff * uPointLightSpecularColors[j];
    546 
    547       LightResult result = _light(viewDirection, normal, lightVector, shininess, metallic);
    548       totalDiffuse += result.diffuse * lightColor;
    549       totalSpecular += result.specular * lightColor * specularColor;
    550     }
    551 
    552     if(j < uSpotLightCount) {
    553       vec3 lightPosition = (uViewMatrix * vec4(uSpotLightLocation[j], 1.0)).xyz;
    554       vec3 lightVector = modelPosition - lightPosition;
    555     
    556       float lightDistance = length(lightVector);
    557       float lightFalloff = 1.0 / (uConstantAttenuation + lightDistance * uLinearAttenuation + (lightDistance * lightDistance) * uQuadraticAttenuation);
    558 
    559       vec3 lightDirection = (uViewMatrix * vec4(uSpotLightDirection[j], 0.0)).xyz;
    560       float spotDot = dot(normalize(lightVector), normalize(lightDirection));
    561       float spotFalloff;
    562       if(spotDot < uSpotLightAngle[j]) {
    563         spotFalloff = 0.0;
    564       }
    565       else {
    566         spotFalloff = pow(spotDot, uSpotLightConc[j]);
    567       }
    568       lightFalloff *= spotFalloff;
    569 
    570       vec3 lightColor = uSpotLightDiffuseColors[j];
    571       vec3 specularColor = uSpotLightSpecularColors[j];
    572      
    573       LightResult result = _light(viewDirection, normal, lightVector, shininess, metallic);
    574       
    575       totalDiffuse += result.diffuse * lightColor * lightFalloff;
    576       totalSpecular += result.specular * lightColor * specularColor * lightFalloff;
    577     }
    578   }
    579 
    580   if( uUseImageLight ){
    581     totalDiffuse += calculateImageDiffuse(normal, modelPosition, metallic);
    582     totalSpecular += calculateImageSpecular(normal, modelPosition, shininess, metallic);
    583   }
    584 
    585   totalDiffuse *= diffuseFactor;
    586   totalSpecular *= specularFactor;
    587 }

    790       // channels by alpha to convert it to premultiplied alpha.

    882 `,Sb=`// include lighting.glsl
    883 precision highp int;
    884 
    885 uniform bool uHasSetAmbient;
    886 uniform vec4 uSpecularMatColor;
    887 uniform vec4 uAmbientMatColor;
    888 uniform vec4 uEmissiveMatColor;
    889 
    890 uniform vec4 uTint;
    891 uniform sampler2D uSampler;
    892 uniform bool isTexture;
    893 
    894 IN vec3 vNormal;
    895 IN vec2 vTexCoord;
    896 IN vec3 vViewPosition;
    897 IN vec3 vAmbientColor;
    898 IN vec4 vColor;
    899 
    900 struct ColorComponents {
    901   vec3 baseColor;
    902   float opacity;
    903   vec3 ambientColor;
    904   vec3 specularColor;
    905   vec3 diffuse;
    906   vec3 ambient;
    907   vec3 specular;
    908   vec3 emissive;
    909 };
    910 
    911 struct Inputs {
    912   vec3 normal;
    913   vec2 texCoord;
    914   vec3 ambientLight;
    915   vec3 ambientMaterial;
    916   vec3 specularMaterial;
    917   vec3 emissiveMaterial;
    918   vec4 color;
    919   float shininess;
    920   float metalness;
    921 };
    922 
    923 void main(void) {
    924   HOOK_beforeFragment();
    925 
    926   Inputs inputs;
    927   inputs.normal = normalize(vNormal);
    928   inputs.texCoord = vTexCoord;
    929   inputs.ambientLight = vAmbientColor;
    930   inputs.color = isTexture
    931       ? TEXTURE(uSampler, vTexCoord) * (vec4(uTint.rgb/255., 1.) * uTint.a/255.)
    932       : vColor;
    933   if (isTexture && inputs.color.a > 0.0) {
    934     // Textures come in with premultiplied alpha. Temporarily unpremultiply it
    935     // so hooks users don't have to think about premultiplied alpha.
    936     inputs.color.rgb /= inputs.color.a;
    937   }
    938   inputs.shininess = uShininess;
    939   inputs.metalness = uMetallic;
    940   inputs.ambientMaterial = uHasSetAmbient ? uAmbientMatColor.rgb : inputs.color.rgb;
    941   inputs.specularMaterial = uSpecularMatColor.rgb;
    942   inputs.emissiveMaterial = uEmissiveMatColor.rgb;
    943   inputs = HOOK_getPixelInputs(inputs);
    944 
    945   vec3 diffuse;
    946   vec3 specular;
    947   totalLight(vViewPosition, inputs.normal, inputs.shininess, inputs.metalness, diffuse, specular);
    948 
    949   // Calculating final color as result of all lights (plus emissive term).
    950 
    951   vec2 texCoord = inputs.texCoord;
    952   vec4 baseColor = inputs.color;
    953   ColorComponents c;
    954   c.opacity = baseColor.a;
    955   c.baseColor = baseColor.rgb;
    956   c.ambientColor = inputs.ambientMaterial;
    957   c.specularColor = inputs.specularMaterial;
    958   c.diffuse = diffuse;
    959   c.ambient = inputs.ambientLight;
    960   c.specular = specular;
    961   c.emissive = inputs.emissiveMaterial;
    962   OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(HOOK_combineColors(c));
    963   OUT_COLOR.rgb *= OUT_COLOR.a; // Premultiply alpha before rendering
    964   HOOK_afterFragment();
    965 }
    966 `,Ab=`IN vec3 aPosition;
    967 IN vec2 aTexCoord;
    968 uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
    969 uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
    970 
    971 uniform vec4 uGlyphRect;
    972 uniform float uGlyphOffset;
    973 
    974 OUT vec2 vTexCoord;
    975 OUT float w;
    976 
    977 void main() {
    978   vec4 positionVec4 = vec4(aPosition, 1.0);
    979 
    980   // scale by the size of the glyph's rectangle
    981   positionVec4.xy *= uGlyphRect.zw - uGlyphRect.xy;
    982 
    983   // Expand glyph bounding boxes by 1px on each side to give a bit of room
    984   // for antialiasing
    985   vec3 newOrigin = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(0., 0., 0., 1.)).xyz;
    986   vec3 newDX = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(1., 0., 0., 1.)).xyz;
    987   vec3 newDY = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(0., 1., 0., 1.)).xyz;
    988   vec2 pixelScale = vec2(
    989     1. / length(newOrigin - newDX),
    990     1. / length(newOrigin - newDY)
    991   );
    992   vec2 offset = pixelScale * normalize(aTexCoord - vec2(0.5, 0.5));
    993   vec2 textureOffset = offset * (1. / vec2(
    994     uGlyphRect.z - uGlyphRect.x,
    995     uGlyphRect.w - uGlyphRect.y
    996   ));
    997 
    998   // move to the corner of the glyph
    999   positionVec4.xy += uGlyphRect.xy;
   1000 
   1001   // move to the letter's line offset
   1002   positionVec4.x += uGlyphOffset;
   1003 
   1004   positionVec4.xy += offset;
   1005   
   1006   gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * uModelViewMatrix * positionVec4;
   1007   vTexCoord = aTexCoord + textureOffset;
   1008   w = gl_Position.w;
   1009 }
   1010 `,Db=`#ifndef WEBGL2
   1011 #extension GL_OES_standard_derivatives : enable
   1012 #endif
   1013 
   1014 #if 0
   1015   // simulate integer math using floats
   1016 	#define int float
   1017 	#define ivec2 vec2
   1018 	#define INT(x) float(x)
   1019 
   1020 	int ifloor(float v) { return floor(v); }
   1021 	ivec2 ifloor(vec2 v) { return floor(v); }
   1022 
   1023 #else
   1024   // use native integer math
   1025 	precision highp int;
   1026 	#define INT(x) x
   1027 
   1028 	int ifloor(float v) { return int(v); }
   1029 	int ifloor(int v) { return v; }
   1030 	ivec2 ifloor(vec2 v) { return ivec2(v); }
   1031 
   1032 #endif
   1033 
   1034 uniform sampler2D uSamplerStrokes;
   1035 uniform sampler2D uSamplerRowStrokes;
   1036 uniform sampler2D uSamplerRows;
   1037 uniform sampler2D uSamplerColStrokes;
   1038 uniform sampler2D uSamplerCols;
   1039 
   1040 uniform ivec2 uStrokeImageSize;
   1041 uniform ivec2 uCellsImageSize;
   1042 uniform ivec2 uGridImageSize;
   1043 
   1044 uniform ivec2 uGridOffset;
   1045 uniform ivec2 uGridSize;
   1046 uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   1047 
   1048 IN vec2 vTexCoord;
   1049 
   1050 // some helper functions
   1051 int ROUND(float v) { return ifloor(v + 0.5); }
   1052 ivec2 ROUND(vec2 v) { return ifloor(v + 0.5); }
   1053 float saturate(float v) { return clamp(v, 0.0, 1.0); }
   1054 vec2 saturate(vec2 v) { return clamp(v, 0.0, 1.0); }
   1055 
   1056 int mul(float v1, int v2) {
   1057   return ifloor(v1 * float(v2));
   1058 }
   1059 
   1060 ivec2 mul(vec2 v1, ivec2 v2) {
   1061   return ifloor(v1 * vec2(v2) + 0.5);
   1062 }
   1063 
   1064 // unpack a 16-bit integer from a float vec2
   1065 int getInt16(vec2 v) {
   1066   ivec2 iv = ROUND(v * 255.0);
   1067   return iv.x * INT(128) + iv.y;
   1068 }
   1069 
   1070 vec2 pixelScale;
   1071 vec2 coverage = vec2(0.0);
   1072 vec2 weight = vec2(0.5);
   1073 const float minDistance = 1.0/8192.0;
   1074 const float hardness = 1.05; // amount of antialias
   1075 
   1076 // the maximum number of curves in a glyph
   1077 const int N = INT(250);
   1078 
   1079 // retrieves an indexed pixel from a sampler
   1080 vec4 getTexel(sampler2D sampler, int pos, ivec2 size) {
   1081   int width = size.x;
   1082   int y = ifloor(pos / width);
   1083   int x = pos - y * width;  // pos % width
   1084 
   1085   return TEXTURE(sampler, (vec2(x, y) + 0.5) / vec2(size));
   1086 }
   1087 
   1088 void calulateCrossings(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2, out vec2 C1, out vec2 C2) {
   1089 
   1090   // get the coefficients of the quadratic in t
   1091   vec2 a = p0 - p1 * 2.0 + p2;
   1092   vec2 b = p0 - p1;
   1093   vec2 c = p0 - vTexCoord;
   1094 
   1095   // found out which values of 't' it crosses the axes
   1096   vec2 surd = sqrt(max(vec2(0.0), b * b - a * c));
   1097   vec2 t1 = ((b - surd) / a).yx;
   1098   vec2 t2 = ((b + surd) / a).yx;
   1099 
   1100   // approximate straight lines to avoid rounding errors
   1101   if (abs(a.y) < 0.001)
   1102     t1.x = t2.x = c.y / (2.0 * b.y);
   1103 
   1104   if (abs(a.x) < 0.001)
   1105     t1.y = t2.y = c.x / (2.0 * b.x);
   1106 
   1107   // plug into quadratic formula to find the corrdinates of the crossings
   1108   C1 = ((a * t1 - b * 2.0) * t1 + c) * pixelScale;
   1109   C2 = ((a * t2 - b * 2.0) * t2 + c) * pixelScale;
   1110 }
   1111 
   1112 void coverageX(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2) {
   1113 
   1114   vec2 C1, C2;
   1115   calulateCrossings(p0, p1, p2, C1, C2);
   1116 
   1117   // determine on which side of the x-axis the points lie
   1118   bool y0 = p0.y > vTexCoord.y;
   1119   bool y1 = p1.y > vTexCoord.y;
   1120   bool y2 = p2.y > vTexCoord.y;
   1121 
   1122   // could web be under the curve (after t1)?
   1123   if (y1 ? !y2 : y0) {
   1124     // add the coverage for t1
   1125     coverage.x += saturate(C1.x + 0.5);
   1126     // calculate the anti-aliasing for t1
   1127     weight.x = min(weight.x, abs(C1.x));
   1128   }
   1129 
   1130   // are we outside the curve (after t2)?
   1131   if (y1 ? !y0 : y2) {
   1132     // subtract the coverage for t2
   1133     coverage.x -= saturate(C2.x + 0.5);
   1134     // calculate the anti-aliasing for t2
   1135     weight.x = min(weight.x, abs(C2.x));
   1136   }
   1137 }
   1138 
   1139 // this is essentially the same as coverageX, but with the axes swapped
   1140 void coverageY(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2) {
   1141 
   1142   vec2 C1, C2;
   1143   calulateCrossings(p0, p1, p2, C1, C2);
   1144 
   1145   bool x0 = p0.x > vTexCoord.x;
   1146   bool x1 = p1.x > vTexCoord.x;
   1147   bool x2 = p2.x > vTexCoord.x;
   1148 
   1149   if (x1 ? !x2 : x0) {
   1150     coverage.y -= saturate(C1.y + 0.5);
   1151     weight.y = min(weight.y, abs(C1.y));
   1152   }
   1153 
   1154   if (x1 ? !x0 : x2) {
   1155     coverage.y += saturate(C2.y + 0.5);
   1156     weight.y = min(weight.y, abs(C2.y));
   1157   }
   1158 }
   1159 
   1160 void main() {
   1161 
   1162   // calculate the pixel scale based on screen-coordinates
   1163   pixelScale = hardness / fwidth(vTexCoord);
   1164 
   1165   // which grid cell is this pixel in?
   1166   ivec2 gridCoord = ifloor(vTexCoord * vec2(uGridSize));
   1167 
   1168   // intersect curves in this row
   1169   {
   1170     // the index into the row info bitmap
   1171     int rowIndex = gridCoord.y + uGridOffset.y;
   1172     // fetch the info texel
   1173     vec4 rowInfo = getTexel(uSamplerRows, rowIndex, uGridImageSize);
   1174     // unpack the rowInfo
   1175     int rowStrokeIndex = getInt16(rowInfo.xy);
   1176     int rowStrokeCount = getInt16(rowInfo.zw);
   1177 
   1178     for (int iRowStroke = INT(0); iRowStroke < N; iRowStroke++) {
   1179       if (iRowStroke >= rowStrokeCount)
   1180         break;
   1181 
   1182       // each stroke is made up of 3 points: the start and control point
   1183       // and the start of the next curve.
   1184       // fetch the indices of this pair of strokes:
   1185       vec4 strokeIndices = getTexel(uSamplerRowStrokes, rowStrokeIndex++, uCellsImageSize);
   1186 
   1187       // unpack the stroke index
   1188       int strokePos = getInt16(strokeIndices.xy);
   1189 
   1190       // fetch the two strokes
   1191       vec4 stroke0 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(0), uStrokeImageSize);
   1192       vec4 stroke1 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(1), uStrokeImageSize);
   1193 
   1194       // calculate the coverage
   1195       coverageX(stroke0.xy, stroke0.zw, stroke1.xy);
   1196     }
   1197   }
   1198 
   1199   // intersect curves in this column
   1200   {
   1201     int colIndex = gridCoord.x + uGridOffset.x;
   1202     vec4 colInfo = getTexel(uSamplerCols, colIndex, uGridImageSize);
   1203     int colStrokeIndex = getInt16(colInfo.xy);
   1204     int colStrokeCount = getInt16(colInfo.zw);
   1205     
   1206     for (int iColStroke = INT(0); iColStroke < N; iColStroke++) {
   1207       if (iColStroke >= colStrokeCount)
   1208         break;
   1209 
   1210       vec4 strokeIndices = getTexel(uSamplerColStrokes, colStrokeIndex++, uCellsImageSize);
   1211 
   1212       int strokePos = getInt16(strokeIndices.xy);
   1213       vec4 stroke0 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(0), uStrokeImageSize);
   1214       vec4 stroke1 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(1), uStrokeImageSize);
   1215       coverageY(stroke0.xy, stroke0.zw, stroke1.xy);
   1216     }
   1217   }
   1218 
   1219   weight = saturate(1.0 - weight * 2.0);
   1220   float distance = max(weight.x + weight.y, minDistance); // manhattan approx.
   1221   float antialias = abs(dot(coverage, weight) / distance);
   1222   float cover = min(abs(coverage.x), abs(coverage.y));
   1223   OUT_COLOR = vec4(uMaterialColor.rgb, 1.) * uMaterialColor.a;
   1224   OUT_COLOR *= saturate(max(antialias, cover));
   1225 }

   1244 #define PROCESSING_LINE_SHADER
   1245 
   1246 #define HOOK_DEFINES
   1247 
   1248 precision highp int;
   1249 precision highp float;
   1250 
   1251 #ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   1252 uniform mat4 uModelMatrix;
   1253 uniform mat4 uViewMatrix;
   1254 #else
   1255 uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   1256 #endif
   1257 
   1258 uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   1259 uniform float uStrokeWeight;
   1260 
   1261 uniform bool uUseLineColor;
   1262 uniform bool uSimpleLines;
   1263 uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   1264 
   1265 uniform vec4 uViewport;
   1266 uniform int uPerspective;
   1267 uniform int uStrokeJoin;
   1268 
   1269 IN vec3 aPosition;
   1270 IN vec3 aTangentIn;
   1271 IN vec3 aTangentOut;
   1272 IN float aSide;
   1273 IN vec4 aVertexColor;
   1274 
   1275 OUT vec4 vColor;
   1276 OUT vec2 vTangent;
   1277 OUT vec2 vCenter;
   1278 OUT vec2 vPosition;
   1279 OUT float vMaxDist;
   1280 OUT float vCap;
   1281 OUT float vJoin;
   1282 OUT float vStrokeWeight;
   1283 
   1284 vec2 lineIntersection(vec2 aPoint, vec2 aDir, vec2 bPoint, vec2 bDir) {
   1285   // Rotate and translate so a starts at the origin and goes out to the right
   1286   bPoint -= aPoint;
   1287   vec2 rotatedBFrom = vec2(
   1288     bPoint.x*aDir.x + bPoint.y*aDir.y,
   1289     bPoint.y*aDir.x - bPoint.x*aDir.y
   1290   );
   1291   vec2 bTo = bPoint + bDir;
   1292   vec2 rotatedBTo = vec2(
   1293     bTo.x*aDir.x + bTo.y*aDir.y,
   1294     bTo.y*aDir.x - bTo.x*aDir.y
   1295   );
   1296   float intersectionDistance =
   1297     rotatedBTo.x + (rotatedBFrom.x - rotatedBTo.x) * rotatedBTo.y /
   1298     (rotatedBTo.y - rotatedBFrom.y);
   1299   return aPoint + aDir * intersectionDistance;
   1300 }
   1301 
   1302 struct StrokeVertex {
   1303   vec3 position;
   1304   vec3 tangentIn;
   1305   vec3 tangentOut;
   1306   vec4 color;
   1307   float weight;
   1308 };
   1309 
   1310 void main() {
   1311   HOOK_beforeVertex();
   1312 
   1313   if (!uSimpleLines) {
   1314       // Caps have one of either the in or out tangent set to 0
   1315       vCap = (aTangentIn == vec3(0.)) != (aTangentOut == vec3(0.)) ? 1. : 0.;
   1316 
   1317       // Joins have two unique, defined tangents
   1318       vJoin = (
   1319           aTangentIn != vec3(0.) &&
   1320           aTangentOut != vec3(0.) &&
   1321           aTangentIn != aTangentOut
   1322       ) ? 1. : 0.;
   1323   }
   1324 
   1325   StrokeVertex inputs;
   1326   inputs.position = aPosition.xyz;
   1327   inputs.color = uUseLineColor ? aVertexColor : uMaterialColor;
   1328   inputs.weight = uStrokeWeight;
   1329   inputs.tangentIn = aTangentIn;
   1330   inputs.tangentOut = aTangentOut;
   1331 
   1332 #ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getObjectInputs
   1333   inputs = HOOK_getObjectInputs(inputs);
   1334 #endif
   1335 
   1336 #ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   1337   inputs.position = (uModelMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   1338   inputs.tangentIn = (uModelMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   1339   inputs.tangentOut = (uModelMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   1340   inputs = HOOK_getWorldInputs(inputs);
   1341 #endif
   1342 
   1343 #ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   1344   // Already multiplied by the model matrix, just apply view
   1345   inputs.position = (uViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   1346   inputs.tangentIn = (uViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   1347   inputs.tangentOut = (uViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   1348 #else
   1349   // Apply both at once
   1350   inputs.position = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   1351   inputs.tangentIn = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   1352   inputs.tangentOut = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   1353 #endif
   1354 #ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getCameraInputs
   1355   inputs = hook_getCameraInputs(inputs);
   1356 #endif
   1357 
   1358   vec4 posp = vec4(inputs.position, 1.);
   1359   vec4 posqIn = vec4(inputs.position + inputs.tangentIn, 1.);
   1360   vec4 posqOut = vec4(inputs.position + inputs.tangentOut, 1.);
   1361   vStrokeWeight = inputs.weight;
   1362 
   1363   float facingCamera = pow(
   1364     // The word space tangent's z value is 0 if it's facing the camera
   1365     abs(normalize(posqIn-posp).z),
   1366 
   1367     // Using pow() here to ramp \`facingCamera\` up from 0 to 1 really quickly
   1368     // so most lines get scaled and don't get clipped
   1369     0.25
   1370   );
   1371 
   1372   // Moving vertices slightly toward the camera
   1373   // to avoid depth-fighting with the fill triangles.
   1374   // A mix of scaling and offsetting is used based on distance
   1375   // Discussion here:
   1376   // https://github.com/processing/p5.js/issues/7200 
   1377 
   1378   // using a scale <1 moves the lines towards nearby camera
   1379   // in order to prevent popping effects due to half of
   1380   // the line disappearing behind the geometry faces.
   1381   float zDistance = -posp.z; 
   1382   float distanceFactor = smoothstep(0.0, 800.0, zDistance); 
   1383   
   1384   // Discussed here:
   1385   // http://www.opengl.org/discussion_boards/ubbthreads.php?ubb=showflat&Number=252848  
   1386   float scale = mix(1., 0.995, facingCamera);
   1387   float dynamicScale = mix(scale, 1.0, distanceFactor); // Closer = more scale, farther = less
   1388 
   1389   posp.xyz = posp.xyz * dynamicScale;
   1390   posqIn.xyz = posqIn.xyz * dynamicScale;
   1391   posqOut.xyz = posqOut.xyz * dynamicScale;
   1392 
   1393   // Moving vertices slightly toward camera when far away 
   1394   // https://github.com/processing/p5.js/issues/6956 
   1395   float zOffset = mix(0., -1., facingCamera);
   1396   float dynamicZAdjustment = mix(0.0, zOffset, distanceFactor); // Closer = less zAdjustment, farther = more
   1397 
   1398   posp.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   1399   posqIn.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   1400   posqOut.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   1401   
   1402   vec4 p = uProjectionMatrix * posp;
   1403   vec4 qIn = uProjectionMatrix * posqIn;
   1404   vec4 qOut = uProjectionMatrix * posqOut;
   1405 
   1406   // formula to convert from clip space (range -1..1) to screen space (range 0..[width or height])
   1407   // screen_p = (p.xy/p.w + <1,1>) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw
   1408 
   1409   // prevent division by W by transforming the tangent formula (div by 0 causes
   1410   // the line to disappear, see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5183)
   1411   // t = screen_q - screen_p
   1412   //
   1413   // tangent is normalized and we don't care which aDirection it points to (+-)
   1414   // t = +- normalize( screen_q - screen_p )
   1415   // t = +- normalize( (q.xy/q.w+<1,1>)*0.5*uViewport.zw - (p.xy/p.w+<1,1>)*0.5*uViewport.zw )
   1416   //
   1417   // extract common factor, <1,1> - <1,1> cancels out
   1418   // t = +- normalize( (q.xy/q.w - p.xy/p.w) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw )
   1419   //
   1420   // convert to common divisor
   1421   // t = +- normalize( ((q.xy*p.w - p.xy*q.w) / (p.w*q.w)) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw )
   1422   //
   1423   // remove the common scalar divisor/factor, not needed due to normalize and +-
   1424   // (keep uViewport - can't remove because it has different components for x and y
   1425   //  and corrects for aspect ratio, see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5181)
   1426   // t = +- normalize( (q.xy*p.w - p.xy*q.w) * uViewport.zw )
   1427 
   1428   vec2 tangentIn = normalize((qIn.xy*p.w - p.xy*qIn.w) * uViewport.zw);
   1429   vec2 tangentOut = normalize((qOut.xy*p.w - p.xy*qOut.w) * uViewport.zw);
   1430 
   1431   vec2 curPerspScale;
   1432   if(uPerspective == 1) {
   1433     // Perspective ---
   1434     // convert from world to clip by multiplying with projection scaling factor
   1435     // to get the right thickness (see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5182)
   1436 
   1437     // The y value of the projection matrix may be flipped if rendering to a Framebuffer.
   1438     // Multiplying again by its sign here negates the flip to get just the scale.
   1439     curPerspScale = (uProjectionMatrix * vec4(1, sign(uProjectionMatrix[1][1]), 0, 0)).xy;
   1440   } else {
   1441     // No Perspective ---
   1442     // multiply by W (to cancel out division by W later in the pipeline) and
   1443     // convert from screen to clip (derived from clip to screen above)
   1444     curPerspScale = p.w / (0.5 * uViewport.zw);
   1445   }
   1446 
   1447   vec2 offset;
   1448   if (vJoin == 1. && !uSimpleLines) {
   1449     vTangent = normalize(tangentIn + tangentOut);
   1450     vec2 normalIn = vec2(-tangentIn.y, tangentIn.x);
   1451     vec2 normalOut = vec2(-tangentOut.y, tangentOut.x);
   1452     float side = sign(aSide);
   1453     float sideEnum = abs(aSide);
   1454 
   1455     // We generate vertices for joins on either side of the centerline, but
   1456     // the "elbow" side is the only one needing a join. By not setting the
   1457     // offset for the other side, all its vertices will end up in the same
   1458     // spot and not render, effectively discarding it.
   1459     if (sign(dot(tangentOut, vec2(-tangentIn.y, tangentIn.x))) != side) {
   1460       // Side enums:
   1461       //   1: the side going into the join
   1462       //   2: the middle of the join
   1463       //   3: the side going out of the join
   1464       if (sideEnum == 2.) {
   1465         // Calculate the position + tangent on either side of the join, and
   1466         // find where the lines intersect to find the elbow of the join
   1467         vec2 c = (posp.xy/posp.w + vec2(1.,1.)) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw;
   1468         vec2 intersection = lineIntersection(
   1469           c + (side * normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.),
   1470           tangentIn,
   1471           c + (side * normalOut * inputs.weight / 2.),
   1472           tangentOut
   1473         );
   1474         offset = (intersection - c);
   1475 
   1476         // When lines are thick and the angle of the join approaches 180, the
   1477         // elbow might be really far from the center. We'll apply a limit to
   1478         // the magnitude to avoid lines going across the whole screen when this
   1479         // happens.
   1480         float mag = length(offset);
   1481         float maxMag = 3. * inputs.weight;
   1482         if (mag > maxMag) {
   1483           offset *= maxMag / mag;
   1484         }
   1485       } else if (sideEnum == 1.) {
   1486         offset = side * normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.;
   1487       } else if (sideEnum == 3.) {
   1488         offset = side * normalOut * inputs.weight / 2.;
   1489       }
   1490     }
   1491     if (uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_BEVEL) {
   1492       vec2 avgNormal = vec2(-vTangent.y, vTangent.x);
   1493       vMaxDist = abs(dot(avgNormal, normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.));
   1494     } else {
   1495       vMaxDist = inputs.weight / 2.;
   1496     }
   1497   } else {
   1498     vec2 tangent = aTangentIn == vec3(0.) ? tangentOut : tangentIn;
   1499     vTangent = tangent;
   1500     vec2 normal = vec2(-tangent.y, tangent.x);
   1501 
   1502     float normalOffset = sign(aSide);
   1503     // Caps will have side values of -2 or 2 on the edge of the cap that
   1504     // extends out from the line
   1505     float tangentOffset = abs(aSide) - 1.;
   1506     offset = (normal * normalOffset + tangent * tangentOffset) *
   1507       inputs.weight * 0.5;
   1508     vMaxDist = inputs.weight / 2.;
   1509   }
   1510 
   1511   vCenter = p.xy;
   1512   vPosition = vCenter + offset;
   1513   vColor = inputs.color;
   1514 
   1515   gl_Position.xy = p.xy + offset.xy * curPerspScale;
   1516   gl_Position.zw = p.zw;
   1517   
   1518   HOOK_afterVertex();
   1519 }
   1520 `,Tb=`precision highp int;
   1521 precision highp float;
   1522 
   1523 uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   1524 uniform int uStrokeCap;
   1525 uniform int uStrokeJoin;
   1526 
   1527 IN vec4 vColor;
   1528 IN vec2 vTangent;
   1529 IN vec2 vCenter;
   1530 IN vec2 vPosition;
   1531 IN float vStrokeWeight;
   1532 IN float vMaxDist;
   1533 IN float vCap;
   1534 IN float vJoin;
   1535 
   1536 float distSquared(vec2 a, vec2 b) {
   1537   vec2 aToB = b - a;
   1538   return dot(aToB, aToB);
   1539 }
   1540 
   1541 struct Inputs {
   1542   vec4 color;
   1543   vec2 tangent;
   1544   vec2 center;
   1545   vec2 position;
   1546   float strokeWeight;
   1547 };
   1548 
   1549 void main() {
   1550   HOOK_beforeFragment();
   1551 
   1552   Inputs inputs;
   1553   inputs.color = vColor;
   1554   inputs.tangent = vTangent;
   1555   inputs.center = vCenter;
   1556   inputs.position = vPosition;
   1557   inputs.strokeWeight = vStrokeWeight;
   1558   inputs = HOOK_getPixelInputs(inputs);
   1559 
   1560   if (vCap > 0.) {
   1561     if (
   1562       uStrokeCap == STROKE_CAP_ROUND &&
   1563       HOOK_shouldDiscard(distSquared(inputs.position, inputs.center) > inputs.strokeWeight * inputs.strokeWeight * 0.25)
   1564     ) {
   1565       discard;
   1566     } else if (
   1567       uStrokeCap == STROKE_CAP_SQUARE &&
   1568       HOOK_shouldDiscard(dot(inputs.position - inputs.center, inputs.tangent) > 0.)
   1569     ) {
   1570       discard;
   1571     // Use full area for PROJECT
   1572     } else if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(false)) {
   1573       discard;
   1574     }
   1575   } else if (vJoin > 0.) {
   1576     if (
   1577       uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_ROUND &&
   1578       HOOK_shouldDiscard(distSquared(inputs.position, inputs.center) > inputs.strokeWeight * inputs.strokeWeight * 0.25)
   1579     ) {
   1580       discard;
   1581     } else if (uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_BEVEL) {
   1582       vec2 normal = vec2(-inputs.tangent.y, inputs.tangent.x);
   1583       if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(abs(dot(inputs.position - inputs.center, normal)) > vMaxDist)) {
   1584         discard;
   1585       }
   1586     // Use full area for MITER
   1587     } else if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(false)) {
   1588       discard;
   1589     }
   1590   }
   1591   OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(vec4(inputs.color.rgb, 1.) * inputs.color.a);
   1592   HOOK_afterFragment();
   1593 }
   1594 `,Nb=`IN vec3 aPosition;
   1595 uniform float uPointSize;
   1596 OUT float vStrokeWeight;
   1597 uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   1598 uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   1599 
   1600 void main() {
   1601   HOOK_beforeVertex();
   1602   vec4 viewModelPosition = vec4(HOOK_getWorldPosition(
   1603     (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(HOOK_getLocalPosition(aPosition), 1.0)).xyz
   1604   ), 1.);
   1605   gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * viewModelPosition;  
   1606 
   1607   float pointSize = HOOK_getPointSize(uPointSize);
   1608 
   1609 	gl_PointSize = pointSize;
   1610 	vStrokeWeight = pointSize;
   1611   HOOK_afterVertex();
   1612 }
   1613 `,Ib=`precision mediump int;
   1614 uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   1615 IN float vStrokeWeight;
   1616 
   1617 void main(){
   1618   HOOK_beforeFragment();
   1619   float mask = 0.0;
   1620 
   1621   // make a circular mask using the gl_PointCoord (goes from 0 - 1 on a point)
   1622   // might be able to get a nicer edge on big strokeweights with smoothstep but slightly less performant
   1623 
   1624   mask = step(0.98, length(gl_PointCoord * 2.0 - 1.0));
   1625 
   1626   // if strokeWeight is 1 or less lets just draw a square
   1627   // this prevents weird artifacting from carving circles when our points are really small
   1628   // if strokeWeight is larger than 1, we just use it as is
   1629 
   1630   mask = mix(0.0, mask, clamp(floor(vStrokeWeight - 0.5),0.0,1.0));
   1631 
   1632   // throw away the borders of the mask
   1633   // otherwise we get weird alpha blending issues
   1634 
   1635   if(HOOK_shouldDiscard(mask > 0.98)){
   1636     discard;
   1637   }
   1638 
   1639   OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(vec4(uMaterialColor.rgb, 1.) * uMaterialColor.a);
   1640   HOOK_afterFragment();
   1641 }
   1642 `,kb=`precision highp float;
   1643 attribute vec3 aPosition;
   1644 attribute vec3 aNormal;
   1645 attribute vec2 aTexCoord;
   1646 
   1647 varying vec3 localPos;
   1648 varying vec3 vWorldNormal;
   1649 varying vec3 vWorldPosition;
   1650 varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   1651 
   1652 uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   1653 uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   1654 uniform mat3 uNormalMatrix;
   1655 
   1656 void main() {
   1657   // Multiply the position by the matrix.
   1658   vec4 viewModelPosition = uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aPosition, 1.0);
   1659   gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * viewModelPosition;  
   1660   
   1661   // orient the normals and pass to the fragment shader
   1662   vWorldNormal = uNormalMatrix * aNormal;
   1663   
   1664   // send the view position to the fragment shader
   1665   vWorldPosition = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aPosition, 1.0)).xyz;
   1666   
   1667   localPos = vWorldPosition;
   1668   vTexCoord = aTexCoord;
   1669 }
   1670 
   1671 
   1672 /*
   1673 in the vertex shader we'll compute the world position and world oriented normal of the vertices and pass those to the fragment shader as varyings.
   1674 */
   1675 `,Mb=`precision highp float;
   1676 varying vec3 localPos;
   1677 
   1678 // the HDR cubemap converted (can be from an equirectangular environment map.)
   1679 uniform sampler2D environmentMap;
   1680 varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   1681 
   1682 const float PI = 3.14159265359;
   1683 
   1684 vec2 nTOE( vec3 v ){
   1685   // x = r sin(phi) cos(theta)   
   1686   // y = r cos(phi)  
   1687   // z = r sin(phi) sin(theta)
   1688   float phi = acos( v.y );
   1689   // if phi is 0, then there are no x, z components
   1690   float theta = 0.0;
   1691   // else 
   1692   theta = acos(v.x / sin(phi));
   1693   float sinTheta = v.z / sin(phi);
   1694   if (sinTheta < 0.0) {
   1695     // Turn it into -theta, but in the 0-2PI range
   1696     theta = 2.0 * PI - theta;
   1697   }
   1698   theta = theta / (2.0 * 3.14159);
   1699   phi = phi / 3.14159 ;
   1700   
   1701   vec2 angles = vec2( phi, theta );
   1702   return angles;
   1703 }
   1704 
   1705 float random(vec2 p) {
   1706   vec3 p3  = fract(vec3(p.xyx) * .1031);
   1707   p3 += dot(p3, p3.yzx + 33.33);
   1708   return fract((p3.x + p3.y) * p3.z);
   1709 }
   1710 
   1711 void main()
   1712 {   	 
   1713 	// the sample direction equals the hemisphere's orientation
   1714   float phi = vTexCoord.x * 2.0 * PI;
   1715   float theta = vTexCoord.y * PI;
   1716   float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);
   1717   float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);
   1718   float z = cos(theta);
   1719   vec3 normal = vec3( x, y, z);
   1720 
   1721 	// Discretely sampling the hemisphere given the integral's
   1722   // spherical coordinates translates to the following fragment code:
   1723 	vec3 irradiance = vec3(0.0);  
   1724 	vec3 up	= vec3(0.0, 1.0, 0.0);
   1725 	vec3 right = normalize(cross(up, normal));
   1726 	up = normalize(cross(normal, right));
   1727 
   1728 	//  We specify a fixed sampleDelta delta value to traverse
   1729   // the hemisphere; decreasing or increasing the sample delta
   1730   // will increase or decrease the accuracy respectively.
   1731 	const float sampleDelta = 0.100;
   1732 	float nrSamples = 0.0;
   1733   float randomOffset = random(gl_FragCoord.xy) * sampleDelta;
   1734 	for(float rawPhi = 0.0; rawPhi < 2.0 * PI; rawPhi += sampleDelta)
   1735 	{
   1736     float phi = rawPhi + randomOffset;
   1737     for(float rawTheta = 0.0; rawTheta < ( 0.5 ) * PI; rawTheta += sampleDelta)
   1738     {
   1739       float theta = rawTheta + randomOffset;
   1740       // spherical to cartesian (in tangent space) // tangent space to world // add each sample result to irradiance
   1741       float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);
   1742       float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);
   1743       float z = cos(theta);
   1744       vec3 tangentSample = vec3( x, y, z);
   1745       
   1746       vec3 sampleVec = tangentSample.x * right + tangentSample.y * up + tangentSample.z * normal;
   1747         irradiance += (texture2D(environmentMap, nTOE(sampleVec)).xyz) * cos(theta) * sin(theta);
   1748       nrSamples++;
   1749     }
   1750 	}
   1751 	// divide by the total number of samples taken, giving us the average sampled irradiance.
   1752 	irradiance = PI * irradiance * (1.0 / float(nrSamples )) ;
   1753   
   1754  
   1755 	gl_FragColor = vec4(irradiance, 1.0);
   1756 }`,Lb=`precision highp float;\r
   1757 varying vec3 localPos;\r
   1758 varying vec2 vTexCoord;\r
   1759 \r
   1760 // our texture\r
   1761 uniform sampler2D environmentMap;\r
   1762 uniform float roughness;\r
   1763 \r
   1764 const float PI = 3.14159265359;\r
   1765 \r
   1766 float VanDerCorput(int bits);\r
   1767 vec2 HammersleyNoBitOps(int i, int N);\r
   1768 vec3 ImportanceSampleGGX(vec2 Xi, vec3 N, float roughness);\r
   1769 \r
   1770 \r
   1771 vec2 nTOE( vec3 v ){\r
   1772   // x = r sin(phi) cos(theta)   \r
   1773   // y = r cos(phi)  \r
   1774   // z = r sin(phi) sin(theta)\r
   1775   float phi = acos( v.y );\r
   1776   // if phi is 0, then there are no x, z components\r
   1777   float theta = 0.0;\r
   1778   // else \r
   1779   theta = acos(v.x / sin(phi));\r
   1780   float sinTheta = v.z / sin(phi);\r
   1781   if (sinTheta < 0.0) {\r
   1782     // Turn it into -theta, but in the 0-2PI range\r
   1783     theta = 2.0 * PI - theta;\r
   1784   }\r
   1785   theta = theta / (2.0 * 3.14159);\r
   1786   phi = phi / 3.14159 ;\r
   1787   \r
   1788   vec2 angles = vec2( phi, theta );\r
   1789   return angles;\r
   1790 }\r
   1791 \r
   1792 \r
   1793 void main(){\r
   1794   const int SAMPLE_COUNT = 400; // 4096\r
   1795   int lowRoughnessLimit = int(pow(2.0,(roughness+0.1)*20.0));\r
   1796   float totalWeight = 0.0;\r
   1797   vec3 prefilteredColor = vec3(0.0);\r
   1798   float phi = vTexCoord.x * 2.0 * PI;\r
   1799   float theta = vTexCoord.y * PI;\r
   1800   float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);\r
   1801   float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);\r
   1802   float z = cos(theta);\r
   1803   vec3 N = vec3(x,y,z);\r
   1804   vec3 V = N;\r
   1805   for (int i = 0; i < SAMPLE_COUNT; ++i)\r
   1806   {\r
   1807     // break at smaller sample numbers for low roughness levels\r
   1808     if(i == lowRoughnessLimit)\r
   1809     {\r
   1810       break;\r
   1811     }\r
   1812     vec2 Xi = HammersleyNoBitOps(i, SAMPLE_COUNT);\r
   1813     vec3 H = ImportanceSampleGGX(Xi, N, roughness);\r
   1814     vec3 L = normalize(2.0 * dot(V, H) * H - V);\r
   1815 \r
   1816     float NdotL = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);\r
   1817     if (NdotL > 0.0)\r
   1818     {\r
   1819       prefilteredColor += texture2D(environmentMap, nTOE(L)).xyz * NdotL;\r
   1820       totalWeight += NdotL;\r
   1821     }\r
   1822   }\r
   1823   prefilteredColor = prefilteredColor / totalWeight;\r
   1824 \r
   1825   gl_FragColor = vec4(prefilteredColor, 1.0);\r
   1826 }\r
   1827 \r
   1828 vec3 ImportanceSampleGGX(vec2 Xi, vec3 N, float roughness){\r
   1829   float a = roughness * roughness;\r
   1830 \r
   1831   float phi = 2.0 * PI * Xi.x;\r
   1832   float cosTheta = sqrt((1.0 - Xi.y) / (1.0 + (a * a - 1.0) * Xi.y));\r
   1833   float sinTheta = sqrt(1.0 - cosTheta * cosTheta);\r
   1834   // from spherical coordinates to cartesian coordinates\r
   1835   vec3 H;\r
   1836   H.x = cos(phi) * sinTheta;\r
   1837   H.y = sin(phi) * sinTheta;\r
   1838   H.z = cosTheta;\r
   1839 \r
   1840   // from tangent-space vector to world-space sample vector\r
   1841   vec3 up = abs(N.z) < 0.999 ? vec3(0.0, 0.0, 1.0) : vec3(1.0, 0.0, 0.0);\r
   1842   vec3 tangent = normalize(cross(up, N));\r
   1843   vec3 bitangent = cross(N, tangent);\r
   1844 \r
   1845   vec3 sampleVec = tangent * H.x + bitangent * H.y + N * H.z;\r
   1846   return normalize(sampleVec);\r
   1847 }\r
   1848 \r
   1849 \r
   1850 float VanDerCorput(int n, int base)\r
   1851 {\r
   1852 #ifdef WEBGL2\r
   1853 \r
   1854     uint bits = uint(n);\r
   1855     bits = (bits << 16u) | (bits >> 16u);\r
   1856     bits = ((bits & 0x55555555u) << 1u) | ((bits & 0xAAAAAAAAu) >> 1u);\r
   1857     bits = ((bits & 0x33333333u) << 2u) | ((bits & 0xCCCCCCCCu) >> 2u);\r
   1858     bits = ((bits & 0x0F0F0F0Fu) << 4u) | ((bits & 0xF0F0F0F0u) >> 4u);\r
   1859     bits = ((bits & 0x00FF00FFu) << 8u) | ((bits & 0xFF00FF00u) >> 8u);\r
   1860     return float(bits) * 2.3283064365386963e-10; // / 0x100000000\r
   1861 \r
   1862 #else\r
   1863 \r
   1864   float invBase = 1.0 / float(base);\r
   1865   float denom = 1.0;\r
   1866   float result = 0.0;\r
   1867 \r
   1868 \r
   1869   for (int i = 0; i < 32; ++i)\r
   1870   {\r
   1871         if (n > 0)\r
   1872         {\r
   1873         denom = mod(float(n), 2.0);\r
   1874         result += denom * invBase;\r
   1875         invBase = invBase / 2.0;\r
   1876         n = int(float(n) / 2.0);\r
   1877         }\r
   1878   }\r
   1879 \r
   1880 \r
   1881   return result;\r
   1882 \r
   1883 #endif\r
   1884 }\r
   1885 \r
   1886 vec2 HammersleyNoBitOps(int i, int N)\r
   1887 {\r
   1888   return vec2(float(i) / float(N), VanDerCorput(i, 2));\r
   1889 }\r
   1890 `,Dc=`precision highp float;

   1928 `,Tc=`// Reduces the bright areas in an image
   1929 
   1930 precision highp float;
   1931 
   1932 varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   1933 
   1934 uniform sampler2D tex0;
   1935 uniform vec2 texelSize;
   1936 
   1937 float luma(vec3 color) {
   1938   // weighted grayscale with luminance values
   1939   // weights 77, 151, 28 taken from src/image/filters.js
   1940   return dot(color, vec3(0.300781, 0.589844, 0.109375));
   1941 }
   1942 
   1943 void main() {
   1944   vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   1945   float lum = luma(color.rgb);
   1946 
   1947   // set current color as the darkest neighbor color
   1948

   1950   neighbors[0] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2( texelSize.x, 0.0));
   1951   neighbors[1] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(-texelSize.x, 0.0));
   1952   neighbors[2] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(0.0,  texelSize.y));

   1961       lum = neighborLum;
   1962     }
   1963   }

   2006 `,Ic=`precision highp float;
   2007 
   2008 // Two-pass blur filter, unweighted kernel.
   2009 // See also a similar blur at Adam Ferriss' repo of shader examples:
   2010 // https://github.com/aferriss/p5jsShaderExamples/blob/gh-pages/4_image-effects/4-9_single-pass-blur/effect.frag
   2011 
   2012 
   2013 uniform sampler2D tex0;
   2014 varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   2015 uniform vec2 direction;
   2016 uniform vec2 canvasSize;
   2017 uniform float radius;
   2018 
   2019 float random(vec2 p) {
   2020   vec3 p3  = fract(vec3(p.xyx) * .1031);
   2021   p3 += dot(p3, p3.yzx + 33.33);
   2022   return fract((p3.x + p3.y) * p3.z);
   2023 }
   2024 
   2025 // This isn't a real Gaussian weight, it's a quadratic weight. It's what the
   2026 // CPU mode's blur uses though, so we also use it here to match.
   2027 float quadWeight(float x, float e) {
   2028   return pow(e-abs(x), 2.);
   2029 }
   2030 
   2031 void main(){
   2032   vec2 uv = vTexCoord;
   2033 
   2034   // A reasonable maximum number of samples
   2035   const float maxSamples = 64.0;
   2036 
   2037   float numSamples = floor(7. * radius);
   2038   if (fract(numSamples / 2.) == 0.) {
   2039     numSamples++;
   2040   }
   2041   vec4 avg = vec4(0.0);
   2042   float total = 0.0;
   2043 
   2044   // Calculate the spacing to avoid skewing if numSamples > maxSamples
   2045   float spacing = 1.0;
   2046   if (numSamples > maxSamples) {
   2047     spacing = numSamples / maxSamples;
   2048     numSamples = maxSamples;
   2049   }
   2050 
   2051   float randomOffset = (spacing - 1.0) * mix(-0.5, 0.5, random(gl_FragCoord.xy));
   2052   for (float i = 0.0; i < maxSamples; i++) {
   2053     if (i >= numSamples) break;
   2054 
   2055     float sample = i * spacing - (numSamples - 1.0) * 0.5 * spacing + randomOffset;
   2056     vec2 sampleCoord = uv + vec2(sample, sample) / canvasSize * direction;
   2057     float weight = quadWeight(sample, (numSamples - 1.0) * 0.5 * spacing);
   2058 
   2059     avg += weight * texture2D(tex0, sampleCoord);
   2060     total += weight;
   2061   }
   2062 
   2063   avg /= total;
   2064   gl_FragColor = avg;
   2065 }
   2066 `,kc=`// Limit color space for a stylized cartoon / poster effect

   2068 precision highp float;

   2070 varying vec2 vTexCoord;

   2072 uniform sampler2D tex0;
   2073 uniform float filterParameter;
   2074 
   2075 vec3 quantize(vec3 color, float n) {
   2076   // restrict values to N options/bins
   2077   // and floor each channel to nearest value
   2078   //
   2079   // eg. when N = 5, values = 0.0, 0.25, 0.50, 0.75, 1.0
   2080   // then quantize (0.1, 0.7, 0.9) -> (0.0, 0.5, 1.0)
   2081 
   2082   color = color * n;
   2083   color = floor(color);
   2084   color = color / (n - 1.0);
   2085   return color;
   2086 }
   2087
